<br>
Have one pull and group, then bring to the other at a designated spot. While moving the quad to the second player, drop at least one quad nuke to ensure keeping aggro. At this time, the puller calls INC. On INC, the second starts looking for his partner and autofollows. The second then switches views to see what is happening. <br>
<br>
The puller has aggro and quads like normal. Just pull a little further than needed to allow for lag between the two players’ computers. Both quad nuke. Wait a brief moment after the pullers spell lands and then pull the quad again with partner in autofollow. (If you are grouping with diffent levels or classes check the cast times of the spells being used.)<br>
<br>
Rinse and repeat. If both partners are good solo quaders, reverse roles and med while the other pulls. This will make up for the few quad nukes on the pull. Since both are splitting the mana cost, the mana regen time is also split and both will keep getting exps equal to solo quading.<br>
<br>
This is a wonderful tactic for friends to use to add a social element to quading. I also use this dual quading tactic to teach friend's secondaries the art of the quad. <br>
<br>
Best of the hunt my friends, <br>
~ Tamroc of Tunare<br>
